    {
      "text": "Osomatsu-kun: Hachamecha Gekijō (おそ松くん はちゃめちゃ劇場; \"Osomatsu-kun: Nonsense Theater\") is a platform video game by Sega, which was released in 1988 for the Sega Mega Drive. An early Mega Drive title, it never saw a release outside of Japan. The game was based on the manga Osomatsu-kun by Fujio Akatsuka, and acts as a promotion for the anime adaptation that premiered the same year. The player controlled the title character and encountered many of the series' characters in a strange, comical world.",
